---
// /home/r_/projects/jeremysayers/src/pages/privacy-policy.astro
import PageIntro from '../components/PageIntro.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Jeremy Sayers"
  description="Privacy policy for JeremySayers.com, including newsletter signup, confirmation, unsubscribe, and email delivery practices."
>
  <PageIntro
    title="Privacy Policy"
    description="This page explains what JeremySayers.com collects, how newsletter signups work, and how email preferences are managed."
  />

  <section class="section-band section-band--paper">
    <div class="shell stack">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="Overview"
        title="Privacy and email signup information for JeremySayers.com."
      />
      <article class="panel">
        <p>
          JeremySayers.com may collect information that visitors provide directly through forms, including newsletter
          signup details and contact information submitted through the site.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-band section-band--warm">
    <div class="shell stack">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="Newsletter"
        title="What is collected and how it is used."
      />
      <article class="panel policy-card">
        <p>
          When you sign up for newsletter updates, the site may collect your email address, first name, last name,
          interests or comments, source page, confirmation and unsubscribe tokens, signup timestamps, limited device
          metadata such as user agent, and a hashed form of your IP address.
        </p>
        <p>
          This information is used to manage subscriptions, send confirmation emails, maintain list hygiene, honor
          unsubscribe requests, and prevent misuse of the signup flow.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-band section-band--paper">
    <div class="shell stack">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="Double Opt-In"
        title="Newsletter subscriptions use email confirmation."
      />
      <article class="panel policy-card">
        <p>
          New newsletter signups are stored as pending until the subscriber confirms through an email link. A
          subscription is not activated until that confirmation step is completed.
        </p>
        <p>
          If a confirmation link expires, the subscriber can request a fresh confirmation email from the site.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-band section-band--slate">
    <div class="shell stack">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="Unsubscribe and Suppression"
        title="Subscribers can unsubscribe at any time."
      />
      <article class="panel policy-card">
        <p>
          Every newsletter email is intended to include an unsubscribe link. When someone unsubscribes, the site marks
          that address accordingly and excludes it from future newsletter sends.
        </p>
        <p>
          The site also maintains suppression and list hygiene states for addresses that should no longer receive
          messages, including unsubscribed, bounced, and complained recipients.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-band section-band--accent">
    <div class="shell stack">
      <SectionHeading
        eyebrow="Delivery and Logging"
        title="Service providers and basic operational logs may be used."
      />
      <article class="panel policy-card">
        <p>
          JeremySayers.com may use third-party email delivery providers to send newsletter confirmation emails and other
          future updates. The email sending layer is structured to support providers such as Resend and similar
          services.
        </p>
        <p>
          The site may also keep limited operational logs related to newsletter events such as signup creation,
          confirmation emails, confirmations, and unsubscribe actions in order to monitor and maintain the system.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
